Jenna Etheridge, News24 Netcare 911 Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cape Town – A cyclist died on the N2 near Shakaskraal on Saturday morning after colliding with an oncoming truck, paramedics said. He had been riding in a group but it is not known what led to the collision, said Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha. Another rider sustained minor injuries but refused treatment. Botha said paramedics found that the truck had driven over the man.They spent about 45 minutes trying to resuscitate him but their efforts were in vain. Police would investigate the accident.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  